1
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:11,000
[TSUKI]
It only takes a tiny leak

2
00:00:11,083 --> 00:00:12,750
to sink a great ship.

3
00:00:12,833 --> 00:00:15,500
No matter how solid
everything else might be,

4
00:00:15,583 --> 00:00:18,125
the smallest crack
can bring about the end.

5
00:00:21,041 --> 00:00:23,166
The one at the top
must always be vigilant

6
00:00:23,250 --> 00:00:24,958
and hyper-aware
of every movement

7
00:00:25,041 --> 00:00:26,291
in their periphery.

8
00:00:28,625 --> 00:00:30,916
I just hope we both live
to see the end of this.

9
00:00:32,625 --> 00:00:36,416
Well, I, I trust you to
take care of this, minister.

10
00:00:37,625 --> 00:00:38,666
Good luck.

11
00:02:12,041 --> 00:02:13,583
[ANNOUNCER] The legendary
long-lost treasure

12
00:02:13,666 --> 00:02:14,958
Tsuki's Tears,

13
00:02:15,041 --> 00:02:17,000
which sank with a luxury liner
in the Pacific

14
00:02:17,083 --> 00:02:19,416
at the beginning
of the 19th century,

15
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:21,208
has now been found.

16
00:02:25,125 --> 00:02:27,416
The discovery was made
by an oceanic research team

17
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:29,166
at Inada University.

18
00:02:29,250 --> 00:02:30,791
The large ruby
is currently valued

19
00:02:30,875 --> 00:02:33,041
at 500 million yen.

20
00:02:36,583 --> 00:02:39,500
[YUJI] Please, you can't
keep doing this.

21
00:02:39,583 --> 00:02:40,750
[exhales]

22
00:02:44,791 --> 00:02:46,250
It's still early.

23
00:02:48,208 --> 00:02:49,916
[KEIGO]
What about you?

24
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,791
What happened to your revenge?

25
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:56,375
You remember
Ryoko's partner, Aoyama?

26
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:01,875
He was found dead. Drowned.

27
00:03:03,375 --> 00:03:05,250
The higher-ups
have shut it down.

28
00:03:05,333 --> 00:03:07,333
Investigation Division.

29
00:03:07,416 --> 00:03:09,666
The chief was transferred out.

30
00:03:09,750 --> 00:03:10,625
[KEIGO]
Hmm.

31
00:03:12,166 --> 00:03:13,500
Please, sir.

32
00:03:13,583 --> 00:03:14,625
[grunts]

33
00:03:14,708 --> 00:03:17,125
I'm just as frustrated as you!

34
00:03:17,208 --> 00:03:19,000
Can't you please tell me
what you know?

35
00:03:20,833 --> 00:03:22,000
The Agency...

36
00:03:23,250 --> 00:03:25,125
just who in the hell are they?

37
00:03:25,208 --> 00:03:26,333
Tell me!

38
00:03:26,416 --> 00:03:27,666
[knock on door]

39
00:03:27,750 --> 00:03:28,875
[door opens]

40
00:03:30,541 --> 00:03:31,875
Detective, um...

41
00:03:34,541 --> 00:03:36,791
[KEIGO]
Hey. It's Mister Famous.

42
00:03:38,750 --> 00:03:42,041
[YOSHIAKI]
You wanted 500,000 yen, right?

43
00:03:42,125 --> 00:03:43,166
[ANNOUNCER]
A few days ago,

44
00:03:43,250 --> 00:03:44,375
the long-lost art piece

45
00:03:44,458 --> 00:03:46,041
known as
Tsuki's Tears was discovered...

46
00:03:46,125 --> 00:03:48,125
I've seen that.

47
00:03:48,208 --> 00:03:49,458
Seen what?

48
00:03:49,541 --> 00:03:51,916
Souma was holding something
just like it.

49
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:55,583
If that's the case,
then it's possible

50
00:03:55,666 --> 00:03:57,583
that you were looking
at an artifact.

51
00:03:57,666 --> 00:03:59,000
[TAKUYA]
An artifact?

52
00:03:59,083 --> 00:04:00,916
I used to work in research.

53
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:03,291
A coworker specialized in them.

54
00:04:03,375 --> 00:04:06,041
Even objects can contain souls.

55
00:04:06,125 --> 00:04:07,875
The will of the one who made it,

56
00:04:07,958 --> 00:04:10,833
and the will of all its owners
throughout the generations.

57
00:04:10,916 --> 00:04:12,666
When those wills combine,

58
00:04:12,750 --> 00:04:15,625
sometimes an item will manifest
a mysterious power.

59
00:04:17,750 --> 00:04:20,041
♪

60
00:04:23,458 --> 00:04:26,583
Why would Souma
carry something like that?

61
00:04:26,666 --> 00:04:28,666
[EIJI] It seems that the power
of objects like those

62
00:04:28,750 --> 00:04:31,791
can magnify
a human's innate abilities.

63
00:04:31,875 --> 00:04:34,583
There are rumors the Agency's
been collecting them

64
00:04:34,666 --> 00:04:36,750
from all over the world.

65
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:38,083
[rapid beeping]

66
00:04:38,166 --> 00:04:40,625
We found him
sniffing around the mansion.

67
00:04:40,708 --> 00:04:42,958
He said he has
some business with Takuya.

68
00:04:43,041 --> 00:04:44,041
What should we do?

69
00:04:45,125 --> 00:04:46,791
[GEEK]
It's the magician.

70
00:04:46,875 --> 00:04:48,416
That guy, Yoshiaki!

71
00:04:54,333 --> 00:04:55,666
When the hell did you have time

72
00:04:55,750 --> 00:04:58,125
to make friends
with such a famous person?

73
00:04:58,208 --> 00:05:00,083
Who was it
that told you about me?

74
00:05:01,333 --> 00:05:03,208
I can't say.

75
00:05:03,291 --> 00:05:04,666
[GEEK]
This is bad.

76
00:05:04,750 --> 00:05:06,125
Doesn't this mean
that someone out there

77
00:05:06,208 --> 00:05:07,541
is looking into Takuya?

78
00:05:08,625 --> 00:05:10,208
So what's your business, then?

79
00:05:12,208 --> 00:05:14,000
The Phantom Thief Brigade X.

80
00:05:14,083 --> 00:05:15,500
Does that happen to ring a bell?

81
00:05:17,875 --> 00:05:20,625
You've come into contact
with them.

82
00:05:20,708 --> 00:05:21,958
A number of times.

83
00:05:22,041 --> 00:05:23,125
Hmm.

84
00:05:24,250 --> 00:05:26,625
♪

85
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,791
[laughs]

86
00:05:32,916 --> 00:05:34,125
Nice try.

87
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,791
[gasps]

88
00:05:37,875 --> 00:05:39,083
♪

89
00:05:44,750 --> 00:05:45,625
[gasps]

90
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:49,375
[groaning]

91
00:05:55,375 --> 00:05:58,291
[YUMIKO] Thanks for the walk
down crappy memory lane.

92
00:05:58,375 --> 00:06:01,583
Okay, so what do you
have to do with them?

93
00:06:01,666 --> 00:06:03,625
[YOSHIAKI]
Their leader, Tsubasa,

94
00:06:03,708 --> 00:06:05,500
he's my older brother.

95
00:06:05,583 --> 00:06:06,625
Seriously?

96
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:11,250
[YOSHIAKI] I haven't seen him
in over ten years, though.

97
00:06:11,333 --> 00:06:13,500
One day, he just up
and disappeared.

98
00:06:13,583 --> 00:06:15,208
[gasps]

99
00:06:15,291 --> 00:06:16,125
[TAKUYA]
And?

100
00:06:17,125 --> 00:06:18,916
[YOSHIAKI]
Look...

101
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,750
I'm here to make a deal.

102
00:06:24,541 --> 00:06:25,791
[YUJI]
Kinda crazy.

103
00:06:25,875 --> 00:06:29,416
Going this far
to meet a long-lost brother.

104
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:31,000
It's weird, isn't it?

105
00:06:31,083 --> 00:06:34,083
I mean, at this point
they're basically strangers.

106
00:06:34,166 --> 00:06:35,708
Yeah, but those two
lost their parents

107
00:06:35,791 --> 00:06:37,833
at a really early age.

108
00:06:37,916 --> 00:06:41,000
They depended on one another
to survive when they were kids.

109
00:06:41,083 --> 00:06:42,416
Oh.

110
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:47,041
Well, the magician is late.
Could be trouble.

111
00:06:47,125 --> 00:06:50,166
You think maybe he told them
about your involvement?

112
00:06:50,250 --> 00:06:53,958
He might be a giant wuss,
but he's not dumb.

113
00:06:54,041 --> 00:06:55,083
Hmm.

114
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:58,000
[YOSHIAKI]
These are the things

115
00:06:58,083 --> 00:07:00,166
the Phantom Thief Brigade
has stolen.

116
00:07:00,250 --> 00:07:02,083
Every one of these
is a piece of art

117
00:07:02,166 --> 00:07:04,125
that's worth hundreds
of millions of yen.

118
00:07:04,208 --> 00:07:07,708
Does that mean they're only
in it for the money, after all?

119
00:07:07,791 --> 00:07:09,041
[YOSHIAKI]
Look at this.

120
00:07:09,125 --> 00:07:11,416
There's a jewel here
called Hoshi's Tears.

121
00:07:11,500 --> 00:07:13,333
[gasps]

122
00:07:13,416 --> 00:07:16,333
You've heard of the recently
recovered Tsuki's Tears?

123
00:07:16,416 --> 00:07:18,875
It's a legendary treasure
that pairs with this item.

124
00:07:20,041 --> 00:07:21,958
I have no doubt
they'll target it.

125
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:24,333
So what you're saying is

126
00:07:24,416 --> 00:07:26,875
that you want me
to catch your brother?

127
00:07:26,958 --> 00:07:29,458
What's in it for us if we do?

128
00:07:29,541 --> 00:07:30,958
Well, plenty, I think.

129
00:07:31,041 --> 00:07:32,833
Recovering the stolen treasures?

130
00:07:33,833 --> 00:07:35,583
Besides, if you catch them,

131
00:07:35,666 --> 00:07:37,875
you'll find out
how they sell the goods.

132
00:07:37,958 --> 00:07:39,500
♪

133
00:07:42,708 --> 00:07:45,333
[RUI] This is
unfinished business, that's all.

134
00:07:45,416 --> 00:07:46,625
Yeah.

135
00:07:48,208 --> 00:07:50,958
Don't see any reason
to ask the boss.

136
00:07:51,041 --> 00:07:52,708
[RUI]
How are things going?

137
00:07:52,791 --> 00:07:54,458
Still researching, stand by.

138
00:07:54,541 --> 00:07:56,250
[humming]

139
00:08:03,041 --> 00:08:05,833
The Phantom Thief Brigade
stole Hoshi's Tears.

140
00:08:05,916 --> 00:08:08,000
But I know the Agency
has it now.

141
00:08:08,083 --> 00:08:10,625
So they're connected
to the Agency?

142
00:08:10,708 --> 00:08:13,750
Takuya, this must be a trap.

143
00:08:13,833 --> 00:08:14,958
Yeah.

144
00:08:18,708 --> 00:08:21,208
I'm sorry,
but I can't trust someone

145
00:08:21,291 --> 00:08:24,125
who won't tell me the source
of their information.

146
00:08:24,208 --> 00:08:27,041
I mean, I really don't want
to do anything rough, but...

147
00:08:28,166 --> 00:08:30,500
Are you sure about that?

148
00:08:30,583 --> 00:08:32,291
I've told my manager.

149
00:08:32,375 --> 00:08:33,916
If anything happens to me,

150
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:36,333
he'll tell the police
and the press about this place.

151
00:08:38,250 --> 00:08:39,750
So you're threatening us now?

152
00:08:39,833 --> 00:08:41,458
That's a problem.

153
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:44,666
[YOSHIAKI]
If I let this chance go,

154
00:08:44,750 --> 00:08:46,708
I'll never see my brother again.

155
00:08:48,875 --> 00:08:50,500
Hmm.

156
00:08:50,583 --> 00:08:53,000
-Hey, um...
-[EIJI] Hmm?

157
00:08:53,083 --> 00:08:57,500
Is it possible an artifact could
change someone's personality?

158
00:08:57,583 --> 00:08:59,083
There's a chance, yeah.

159
00:08:59,166 --> 00:09:00,416
[gasps]

160
00:09:01,625 --> 00:09:03,916
If we examine Tsuki's Tears,

161
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:06,958
maybe we could find some way
to change Souma back.

162
00:09:08,333 --> 00:09:09,583
Hmm.

163
00:09:09,666 --> 00:09:10,875
Jeez.

164
00:09:16,416 --> 00:09:19,333
-[keyboard keys clacking]
-Infiltration successful.

165
00:09:19,416 --> 00:09:22,000
Hey, what's your brother's deal?

166
00:09:22,083 --> 00:09:24,041
Why's he leading
the Phantom Thief Brigade?

167
00:09:25,291 --> 00:09:27,125
[YOSHIAKI]
I don't know.

168
00:09:27,208 --> 00:09:29,750
[TAKUYA] He's been super quiet
ever since the Lost.

169
00:09:29,833 --> 00:09:31,916
What's he been doing lately?

170
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:33,375
[YOSHIAKI]
I don't know.

171
00:09:33,458 --> 00:09:35,750
[TAKUYA] Not the tightest
of brothers then, huh?

172
00:09:39,208 --> 00:09:41,291
[WOMAN 1] They say it was
a traffic accident.

173
00:09:41,375 --> 00:09:42,583
[WOMAN 2]
How terrible.

174
00:09:42,666 --> 00:09:44,791
[WOMAN 1]
Her children are still so young.

175
00:09:44,875 --> 00:09:47,125
♪

176
00:09:54,458 --> 00:09:56,125
[YUKI]
Father.

177
00:09:56,208 --> 00:09:59,166
I promise, I'll work hard.

178
00:10:07,875 --> 00:10:10,375
Souma will be fine.

179
00:10:10,458 --> 00:10:11,958
I'll make sure of it.

180
00:10:16,250 --> 00:10:18,708
♪

181
00:10:29,708 --> 00:10:32,500
How long are we gonna
tail these guys?

182
00:10:32,583 --> 00:10:35,375
And how is some dumb magician
supposed to help us?

183
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:37,791
Hmm?

184
00:10:37,875 --> 00:10:39,958
[KEIGO] We're following
this man named Takuya.

185
00:10:40,041 --> 00:10:42,666
He was the last person
she was chasing after.

186
00:10:44,291 --> 00:10:48,833
And in the past, he's been known
to be involved with the Agency.

187
00:10:48,916 --> 00:10:51,000
[YUJI] You should've told me
that from the start.

188
00:10:52,041 --> 00:10:53,458
[yells]

189
00:11:00,250 --> 00:11:02,041
Whoa! What the hell?

190
00:11:02,125 --> 00:11:03,166
Did you guys see that?

191
00:11:03,250 --> 00:11:05,083
Oh, um...

192
00:11:06,708 --> 00:11:07,708
Well, I'm...

193
00:11:07,791 --> 00:11:09,208
I'm a magician and all.

194
00:11:11,291 --> 00:11:12,208
But that was...

195
00:11:14,333 --> 00:11:15,208
[SOUMA]
So?

196
00:11:16,875 --> 00:11:18,375
Any thoughts on my plan?

197
00:11:19,375 --> 00:11:20,916
I mean, it'd be boring
if we just got

198
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:23,875
a backup for this thing,
don't you think?

199
00:11:23,958 --> 00:11:25,416
I know I do.

200
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:28,041
Let's take this chance
to roundup those artifacts.

201
00:11:28,125 --> 00:11:31,291
And we should use
that guy to do it, Tsubasa.

202
00:11:31,375 --> 00:11:33,791
[TSUKI] You think it'll be
as easy as that?

203
00:11:33,875 --> 00:11:35,625
[SOUMA]
Don't look down on me, old lady.

204
00:11:35,708 --> 00:11:36,625
You little...

205
00:11:36,708 --> 00:11:38,250
They'll totally take the bait,

206
00:11:38,333 --> 00:11:39,583
won't they?

207
00:11:39,666 --> 00:11:41,458
Yes. No doubt.

208
00:11:41,541 --> 00:11:43,958
This girl has already
failed us once.

209
00:11:44,041 --> 00:11:46,333
We can't leave things
to her again.

210
00:11:46,416 --> 00:11:48,125
If we do that, we're fools.

211
00:11:48,208 --> 00:11:49,958
-Oh, I don't know.
-Huh?

212
00:11:50,041 --> 00:11:52,208
Experience is important.

213
00:11:53,208 --> 00:11:54,208
Hmm.

214
00:11:54,291 --> 00:11:56,666
[SOUMA scoffs]
Too bad for you.

215
00:11:56,750 --> 00:11:58,750
-Let's go, Suzuna.
-Right.

216
00:12:00,208 --> 00:12:02,625
[door opens and closes]

217
00:12:02,708 --> 00:12:03,833
[sighs]

218
00:12:03,916 --> 00:12:05,375
How troublesome.

219
00:12:05,458 --> 00:12:07,958
We should have just
brainwashed the boy.

220
00:12:08,041 --> 00:12:09,833
[TAIYO]
He's more interesting this way.

221
00:12:09,916 --> 00:12:13,000
Kids are cuter when they're
a little bit cheeky.

222
00:12:14,750 --> 00:12:17,291
But I'm the one
who gets inconvenienced.

223
00:12:17,375 --> 00:12:20,875
I'd very much prefer not to get
bitten by yet another pet dog.

224
00:12:20,958 --> 00:12:23,916
♪

225
00:12:28,250 --> 00:12:29,250
[YUJI]
Huh?

226
00:12:29,333 --> 00:12:30,833
[KEIGO]
What is it?

227
00:12:30,916 --> 00:12:32,333
[YUJI]
Nothing.

228
00:12:32,416 --> 00:12:34,375
-Uh-oh.
-[ALL] Hmm?

229
00:12:34,458 --> 00:12:36,625
♪

230
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:39,875
[KANA]
Hey. Found you.

231
00:12:39,958 --> 00:12:40,916
Yep, this is bad!

232
00:12:43,208 --> 00:12:45,625
-Oh, crap.
-Be careful.

233
00:12:45,708 --> 00:12:48,166
♪

234
00:12:52,916 --> 00:12:54,375
[tires screeching]

235
00:13:01,625 --> 00:13:03,083
What happened?

236
00:13:03,166 --> 00:13:05,166
[DRIVER] Someone attacked us
right outta the blue!

237
00:13:05,250 --> 00:13:07,291
[groans]

238
00:13:07,375 --> 00:13:08,208
Huh?

239
00:13:08,291 --> 00:13:10,500
[laughs]
You lose, dude.

240
00:13:10,583 --> 00:13:13,125
I'm afraid we'll be the ones
taking Tsuki's Tears.

241
00:13:13,208 --> 00:13:15,458
Have a nice day.

242
00:13:15,541 --> 00:13:17,458
[TAKUYA]
They're playing with us.

243
00:13:17,541 --> 00:13:18,541
[YUMIKO]
Everyone all right?

244
00:13:20,291 --> 00:13:23,041
Ow, ow, ow. It's fine.

245
00:13:23,125 --> 00:13:25,958
I just found out where
they're keeping Tsuki's Tears.

246
00:13:26,041 --> 00:13:27,250
[YUMIKO]
Not in their research tower?

247
00:13:27,333 --> 00:13:28,625
Nuh-uh.

248
00:13:28,708 --> 00:13:29,875
And it looks like
they're moving it

249
00:13:29,958 --> 00:13:31,833
to a different spot tonight.

250
00:13:31,916 --> 00:13:34,625
Tomorrow, important people are
apparently gathering to see it.

251
00:13:34,708 --> 00:13:39,083
Well, either way,
we can't move forward like this.

252
00:13:39,166 --> 00:13:42,208
My brother.
How could he do this?

253
00:13:45,250 --> 00:13:46,875
[water falling]

254
00:13:53,666 --> 00:13:54,833
Hmm.

255
00:13:57,166 --> 00:13:59,083
[MAN 1]
You want to retract your bid?

256
00:13:59,166 --> 00:14:01,375
No, you can't be serious.

257
00:14:01,458 --> 00:14:04,250
[MAN 2] Prime real estate
like this isn't easy to come by.

258
00:14:04,333 --> 00:14:06,125
[TSUKI] We're making
some rather drastic changes

259
00:14:06,208 --> 00:14:07,625
to our business plans.

260
00:14:07,708 --> 00:14:09,000
[MAN 3]
Are you sure?

261
00:14:09,083 --> 00:14:11,416
I'm afraid the penalties
will be awfully high.

262
00:14:11,500 --> 00:14:13,583
[TSUKI]
Yes. That's not a problem.

263
00:14:15,083 --> 00:14:17,541
[TAIYO]
In the end, it will all be gone.

264
00:14:17,625 --> 00:14:19,208
-[MAN 3] What?
-[thuds]

265
00:14:21,458 --> 00:14:22,500
[gasps]

266
00:14:22,583 --> 00:14:24,375
-[explosions]
-[gas hissing]

267
00:14:24,458 --> 00:14:26,166
-[MEN coughing]
-[MAN 2] What's happening?

268
00:14:30,333 --> 00:14:31,625
[yells]

269
00:14:32,625 --> 00:14:33,916
[groans]

270
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:36,333
♪

271
00:14:36,416 --> 00:14:37,916
[whimpers, gasps]

272
00:14:38,916 --> 00:14:40,208
[gasps]

273
00:14:40,291 --> 00:14:41,833
-[gunshot]
-[groans sharply]

274
00:14:41,916 --> 00:14:43,416
[panting]

275
00:14:46,916 --> 00:14:48,291
You're such a failure.

276
00:14:51,291 --> 00:14:52,458
[TSUBASA]
Shit!

277
00:14:53,666 --> 00:14:55,000
♪

278
00:15:00,541 --> 00:15:01,875
[gasps]

279
00:15:04,708 --> 00:15:06,000
[TAKUYA]
Tsubasa's data?

280
00:15:06,083 --> 00:15:07,791
Yes, it was still in

281
00:15:07,875 --> 00:15:10,125
the detective agency's database.

282
00:15:10,208 --> 00:15:11,291
Look at this.

283
00:15:11,375 --> 00:15:12,458
It's the institution

284
00:15:12,541 --> 00:15:14,208
he was in as a child.

285
00:15:14,291 --> 00:15:17,500
[TAKUYA] "Light of Hope Academy
for Disabled Children."

286
00:15:17,583 --> 00:15:19,583
Yoshiaki, too, then.

287
00:15:19,666 --> 00:15:20,916
Probably so.

288
00:15:22,791 --> 00:15:24,208
[TAKUYA]
Poor guy.

289
00:15:24,291 --> 00:15:25,916
Who do you think
put him up to this?

290
00:15:29,041 --> 00:15:31,375
[crying]

291
00:15:31,458 --> 00:15:32,791
♪

292
00:15:35,208 --> 00:15:38,375
[TSUBASA chuckles]
Are you crying again, Yoshiaki?

293
00:15:38,458 --> 00:15:41,125
Brother, it hurts.

294
00:15:41,208 --> 00:15:43,291
[crying]

295
00:15:47,458 --> 00:15:49,250
[TSUBASA]
Come on, don't cry.

296
00:15:49,333 --> 00:15:51,291
Here. Watch this, okay?

297
00:15:57,208 --> 00:16:00,208
Oh, wow. It disappeared.

298
00:16:00,291 --> 00:16:02,250
Along with those tears, right?

299
00:16:07,375 --> 00:16:08,916
From Takuya.

300
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:10,458
Oh, thank you.

301
00:16:16,166 --> 00:16:17,541
[YUKI]
What kind of person was he?

302
00:16:18,583 --> 00:16:21,083
-[YOSHIAKI] Huh?
-[YUKI] Your brother.

303
00:16:21,166 --> 00:16:22,291
[YOSHIAKI]
Oh.

304
00:16:22,375 --> 00:16:24,541
He was a pretty cool
big brother.

305
00:16:24,625 --> 00:16:26,791
But he was a strange person.

306
00:16:26,875 --> 00:16:28,833
In what way?

307
00:16:28,916 --> 00:16:30,166
For instance,

308
00:16:30,250 --> 00:16:32,333
how do you eat
fried pork cutlets?

309
00:16:32,416 --> 00:16:34,875
Huh? I don't know.

310
00:16:34,958 --> 00:16:36,541
With sauce, like normal?

311
00:16:36,625 --> 00:16:38,458
'Course you do.

312
00:16:38,541 --> 00:16:39,833
My brother takes
the breading off

313
00:16:39,916 --> 00:16:41,583
before he eats them.

314
00:16:41,666 --> 00:16:43,458
-Huh?
-Weird, right?

315
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:48,666
Even with siblings,

316
00:16:48,750 --> 00:16:51,208
I guess there are things
you'll never understand.

317
00:16:53,208 --> 00:16:54,333
Yeah.

318
00:17:06,791 --> 00:17:09,250
We don't need you
around anymore, Akira.

319
00:17:10,625 --> 00:17:12,208
Some security guy.

320
00:17:12,291 --> 00:17:14,458
Couldn't even keep her safe.

321
00:17:16,041 --> 00:17:17,833
Don't worry about us
from now on.

322
00:17:17,916 --> 00:17:20,458
Why don't you go hang around
Dad or something?

323
00:17:20,541 --> 00:17:23,416
Your father has
ordered me to stay here.

324
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:24,375
[grunts]

325
00:17:26,041 --> 00:17:27,958
Mind your own business!

326
00:17:28,041 --> 00:17:30,208
[gasps]
What's wrong, Souma?!

327
00:17:30,291 --> 00:17:31,791
[SOUMA grunts]

328
00:17:40,083 --> 00:17:42,500
[GEEK] The Phantom Thief Brigade
is definitely around.

329
00:17:46,916 --> 00:17:49,208
[KANA] Those guys showed up,
just like we thought.

330
00:17:49,291 --> 00:17:51,750
They're not getting off
with a warning this time.

331
00:17:51,833 --> 00:17:53,500
They simply refuse to learn.

332
00:17:53,583 --> 00:17:55,708
Let's just get this over with.

333
00:17:58,708 --> 00:17:59,666
-[rattles]
-[gasps]

334
00:17:59,750 --> 00:18:00,875
-Hmm?
-[gasps]

335
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:06,583
[SOUMA] Are you guys
that Phantom Thief Brigade?

336
00:18:06,666 --> 00:18:08,625
That a kid?

337
00:18:08,708 --> 00:18:11,375
Shouldn't you be in bed already?

338
00:18:11,458 --> 00:18:13,416
[SOUMA]
More like the cosplay brigade.

339
00:18:13,500 --> 00:18:16,250
Didn't you hear?
Halloween's come and gone.

340
00:18:16,333 --> 00:18:17,583
What'd you say?

341
00:18:20,541 --> 00:18:22,875
How'd you get that?

342
00:18:22,958 --> 00:18:25,000
What are you doing with it
in the first place?

343
00:18:27,250 --> 00:18:29,250
[coughs]

344
00:18:29,333 --> 00:18:30,750
[RUI]
Check it out, boss.

345
00:18:32,083 --> 00:18:33,666
[ALL chuckle]

346
00:18:35,625 --> 00:18:37,291
[TSUBASA]
What the...

347
00:18:37,375 --> 00:18:39,541
[JACK] All it means
is that we're fine on our own.

348
00:18:40,583 --> 00:18:41,958
It's okay.

349
00:18:42,041 --> 00:18:44,083
We'll all survive
if you wanna rest like this

350
00:18:44,166 --> 00:18:45,500
every once in a while.

351
00:18:45,583 --> 00:18:46,833
[TSUBASA breathes heavily]

352
00:18:46,916 --> 00:18:49,791
Sorry, I'll pull my weight
next time.

353
00:18:49,875 --> 00:18:52,666
But seriously,
how'd you guys manage it?

354
00:18:52,750 --> 00:18:54,625
[laughs]

355
00:18:54,708 --> 00:18:55,625
[TSUBASA]
Huh? What is it?

356
00:18:55,708 --> 00:18:56,791
What is it?

357
00:18:56,875 --> 00:18:58,541
[TSUBASA laughing]

358
00:18:58,625 --> 00:19:01,500
This is a fake.

359
00:19:01,583 --> 00:19:04,000
-[RUI] What?!
-[KANA gasps]

360
00:19:04,083 --> 00:19:07,000
[JACK] That has to mean
that they knew we were after it.

361
00:19:07,083 --> 00:19:09,583
[KANA]
How? No way.

362
00:19:09,666 --> 00:19:11,541
-[TSUBASA] Eh, don't worry.
-[ALL] Hmm?

363
00:19:11,625 --> 00:19:13,958
This is still pretty nice.

364
00:19:14,041 --> 00:19:15,291
It's a good little trinket.

365
00:19:17,208 --> 00:19:18,083
See?

366
00:19:19,250 --> 00:19:20,666
It's beautiful up there.

367
00:19:20,750 --> 00:19:22,916
I knew this chandelier
was missing something.

368
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:24,250
[BOTH gasp]

369
00:19:25,625 --> 00:19:26,833
[gasps]

370
00:19:28,875 --> 00:19:30,250
When it came down to it,
in the end,

371
00:19:30,333 --> 00:19:32,875
we never found the real thing.

372
00:19:32,958 --> 00:19:35,666
Anyway, who the hell are you?

373
00:19:35,750 --> 00:19:37,208
Who knows, right?

374
00:19:38,625 --> 00:19:40,250
Perfect timing.

375
00:19:40,333 --> 00:19:43,750
This way, we can steal it
right along with Tsuki's Tears.

376
00:19:43,833 --> 00:19:46,916
It'll make our leader
very happy.

377
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:48,791
Are you guys really that stupid?

378
00:19:48,875 --> 00:19:50,166
-[SUMIRE] Hmm?
-[RUI] Huh?

379
00:19:51,625 --> 00:19:52,791
[ALL gasp]

380
00:19:56,250 --> 00:19:58,583
Tsuki's Tears is gone?

381
00:19:58,666 --> 00:19:59,500
But how?

382
00:19:59,583 --> 00:20:01,041
Was it him?

383
00:20:01,125 --> 00:20:02,125
My brother?

384
00:20:03,291 --> 00:20:04,541
-[loud thud]
-[SUMIRE screams]

385
00:20:08,083 --> 00:20:09,875
[gasps]

386
00:20:09,958 --> 00:20:11,208
[YUKI]
Souma!

387
00:20:11,291 --> 00:20:13,708
Hey, there, sis.
[chuckles]

388
00:20:13,791 --> 00:20:15,708
The hell's going on?

389
00:20:15,791 --> 00:20:18,708
Lucky me,
running into you like this.

390
00:20:18,791 --> 00:20:20,916
Thank goodness.

391
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:23,416
Thank goodness
you're all right.

392
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:24,625
[gasps]

393
00:20:25,875 --> 00:20:28,875
What, are you this kid's
allies or something?

394
00:20:28,958 --> 00:20:30,666
Better think carefully
about your answer.

395
00:20:30,750 --> 00:20:33,458
You're all his subordinates,
aren't you?

396
00:20:33,541 --> 00:20:35,375
Why is he holding
Hoshi's Tears?

397
00:20:35,458 --> 00:20:37,166
The thing you guys stole.

398
00:20:37,250 --> 00:20:39,208
[RUI]
We have the same question!

399
00:20:39,291 --> 00:20:42,000
Are you sure you guys
should be bickering right now?

400
00:20:42,083 --> 00:20:44,291
There's no time for that.
Tell me where you've hidden

401
00:20:44,375 --> 00:20:46,208
all the artifacts
that you've stolen.

402
00:20:46,291 --> 00:20:48,250
If you don't,

403
00:20:48,333 --> 00:20:49,708
then she's gonna die.

404
00:20:49,791 --> 00:20:51,750
♪

405
00:21:01,791 --> 00:21:03,250
[shuddering]

406
00:21:05,625 --> 00:21:07,208
I'll tell you
what you wanna know.

407
00:21:07,291 --> 00:21:09,000
You're messing
with the wrong people,

408
00:21:09,083 --> 00:21:10,166
you little brat.

409
00:21:10,250 --> 00:21:11,041
[yells]

410
00:21:11,125 --> 00:21:13,833
♪

411
00:21:16,708 --> 00:21:17,875
[grunts]

412
00:21:22,875 --> 00:21:24,041
-[gasps]
-No way.

413
00:21:29,083 --> 00:21:31,000
[BOTH groan]

414
00:21:31,083 --> 00:21:33,166
This is starting
to get troublesome.

415
00:21:33,250 --> 00:21:34,666
Please stop this.

416
00:21:34,750 --> 00:21:36,875
Maybe I should just
kill all of you now.

417
00:21:36,958 --> 00:21:38,541
Souma, stop it!

418
00:21:38,625 --> 00:21:39,791
Tch.

419
00:21:39,875 --> 00:21:41,250
More to the point.

420
00:21:42,291 --> 00:21:44,208
Why the hell
are you still alive?!

421
00:21:44,291 --> 00:21:45,833
♪

422
00:21:45,916 --> 00:21:47,375
[gunshots]

423
00:21:53,750 --> 00:21:54,916
[grunts softly]

424
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:56,375
Well, what have we here?

425
00:22:00,833 --> 00:22:02,416
Long time, no see...

426
00:22:04,041 --> 00:22:05,208
Akira.

427
00:23:44,041 --> 00:23:46,291
[YUKI]
Next Episode, "Parting."

